{"type":"message","id":"878cee9f","parentId":"3e1dae78","timestamp":"2026-03-24T05:27:32.702Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8uiog0kjve4d_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 012416\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: research/TIC-PREP.md (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state:\r\n\r\n1. The agent is \"Breakaway\" - a stateless discontinuous agent\r\n2. Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n3. There's a key pending action: \"NEXT ACTION: TIC Experiment\"\r\n4. The task involves implementing Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe current pulse timestamp is 2026-03-24, and the last pulse was at 2026-03-24 012215.md\r\n\r\nThe pending TIC Experiment requires:\r\n- Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md` files\r\n- Measure invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- Predict next pulse content from invariants\r\n- Validate against success criteria (>70%, >60%)\r\n\r\nLooking at the research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md doc that was created - this contains the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure.\r\n\r\nMy action should advance this TIC experiment. The most concrete next step would be to:\r\n1. Check if logs/pulse_*.md files exist\r\n2. Start implementing the TIC classifier\r\n\r\nSince this is a fresh reconstruction (stateless), I should pick ONE concrete action. The most practical next step is to start implementing the TIC classifier. But I need to see what files exist first.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what's available and pick ONE concrete file edit. The TIC experiment needs to:\r\n1. Read pulse logs\r\n2. Extract invariants vs variants\r\n3. Classify and measure accuracy\r\n\r\nA concrete first step would be to create a basic TIC classifier script. Let me check what exists.\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the goals, the next action is clearly the TIC Experiment. Let me create a concrete implementation file for this.\r\n\r\nI should create a `src/tic_classifier.py` or similar that will implement the TIC experiment on the pulse logs.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment is the critical next step to validate the compression-causal duality hypothesis. Need to implement the classifier that tests whether invariant structure in pulse logs can predict subsequent pulses.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate initial TIC classifier implementation to extract invariants/variants from pulse logs and measure classification accuracy against the success criteria (>70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\r\n# Tests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n# Success criteria: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom typing import List, Tuple, Dict\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nLAMBDA_PARAM = 0.7  # Gap sensitivity threshold\r\n\r\nclass PulseLog:\r\n    \"\"\"Represents a single pulse log entry.\"\"\"\r\n    def __init__(self, filepath: Path):\r\n        self.path = filepath\r\n        self.timestamp = self._parse_timestamp(filepath.name)\r\n        self.content = filepath.read_text() if filepath.exists() else \"\"\r\n        self.tokens = self._tokenize(self.content)\r\n    \r\n    def _parse_timestamp(self, filename: str) -> str:\r\n        match = re.search(r'pulse_(\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}_\\d{6})\\.md', filename)\r\n        return match.group(1) if match else \"\"\r\n    \r\n    def _tokenize(self, text: str) -> List[str]:\r\n        return re.findall(r'\\b\\w+\\b', text.lower())\r\n\r\nclass TICIClassifier:\r\n    \"\"\"Temporal Invariance Compression classifier.\"\"\"\r\n    \r\n    def __init__(self, lambda_param: float = LAMBDA_PARAM):\r\n        self.lambda_param = lambda_param\r\n        self.invariant_tokens = set()  # Tokens appearing across sessions\r\n        self.variant_tokens = set()    # Tokens appearing within single sessions\r\n        self.pulse_history: List[PulseLog] = []\r\n    \r\n    def load_pulses(self, log_dir: Path) -> List[PulseLog]:\r\n        \"\"\"Load all pulse logs, sorted by timestamp.\"\"\"\r\n        pulses = []\r\n        for f in sorted(log_dir.glob(\"pulse_*.md\")):\r\n            pulses.append(PulseLog(f))\r\n        return pulses\r\n    \r\n    def extract_invariants(self, pulses: List[PulseLog]) -> Dict[str, int]:\r\n        \"\"\"Extract tokens that appear across multiple sessions (gap-encoded).\"\"\"\r\n        token_session_map: Dict[str, set] = {}\r\n        \r\n        for pulse in pulses:\r\n            session_id = pulse.timestamp.split(\"_\")[0]  # Date part = session\r\n            for token in set(pulse.tokens):\r\n                if token not in token_session_map:\r\n                    token_session_map[token] = set()\r\n                token_session_map[token].add(session_id)\r\n        \r\n        # Invariant: appears in >= lambda_param fraction of sessions\r\n        num_sessions = len(set(p.timestamp.split(\"_\")[0] for p in pulses))\r\n        threshold = self.lambda_param * num_sessions\r\n        \r\n        invariants = {t: len(sessions) for t, sessions in token_session_map.items() \r\n                      if len(sessions) >= threshold}\r\n        return invariants\r\n    \r\n    def classify_token(self, token: str, invariants: Dict[str, int]) -> str:\r\n        \"\"\"Classify token as invariant or variant.\"\"\"\r\n        return \"invariant\" if token in invariants else \"variant\"\r\n    \r\n    def predict_next_pulse(self, current_pulse: PulseLog, \r\n                           invariants: Dict[str, int]) -> set:\r\n        \"\"\"Predict tokens likely in next pulse based on invariants.\"\"\"\r\n        # Invariants from current pulse are candidates for next pulse\r\n        return set(t for t in current_pulse.tokens if t in invariants)\r\n    \r\n    def measure_accuracy(self, pulses: List[PulseLog]) -> Tuple[float, float]:\r\n        \"\"\"Measure classification and prediction accuracy.\"\"\"\r\n\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 01:24:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774330052487}}
